  "_comment": "Landscape generation config. Wildkin does NOT use a fixed, hand-drawn map — every new sanctuary generates its own terrain from a random seed + one of the biomes below, so every player's land (and every 'Reset & new land') looks different. `tileTypes` is the registry of every tile that can exist (placeholder colors for now). Each biome picks a base ground, a patch terrain, a liquid, and a trail tile, plus generation knobs: how many liquid pools / terrain patches / trails to carve and how big. `nodes` is how many of each resource node type spawn. Add a biome by adding tiles + one biome entry — no code changes. ART PASS: tile types with a `sprite` render real diamond art from public/assets/wildkin/tiles/<sprite>.png (others keep the drawn placeholder).",
